One of These Declarations Is Not Like the Others
------------------------------------------------

This Thursday, two very different versions of the Declaration of
Independence will go head-to-head at Christie=E2=80=99s and Sotheby=E2=80=
=99s in New York. In its 10 a.m. Americana auction, Christie=E2=80=99s is o=
ffering the =E2=80=9CThe Jones Declaration of Independence ( https://www.ch=
risties.com/en/lot/lot-the-jones-declaration-of-independence-6519108/?utm_c=
ampaign=3DWall+Power+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%281%2F21%2F25%29&utm_content=3DWall+Pow=
er+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%281%2F21%2F25%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dc=
ustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ),=E2=80=9D a handwritten transcri=
ption of the original document that was produced in 1788=E2=80=9412 years a=
fter independence was declared. Then at 2 p.m., Sotheby=E2=80=99s New York =
is selling
=E2=80=9CThe Declaration of Independence: The July 1776 Exeter Broadside ( =
https://www.sothebys.com/en/buy/auction/2025/the-declaration-of-independenc=
e-the-july-1776-essex-broadside?locale=3Den&utm_campaign=3DWall+Power+-+SUB=
